#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:2 3af2a483ba9b4326a9b24cf13a125b47
msgid "Discord"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:4 f61edd81b518453eb3c68b2f70433329
msgid ""
"Real-time chat with the TensorMesh community — quick help, design "
"discussions, and showing off what you've built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:7 049359e264f44929894ac793deb9bfb0
msgid ""
"The Discord server is the right place when you want a fast, "
"conversational back-and-forth. For long-form Q&A that future users will "
"find via search, prefer :doc:`github_discussions`. For bug reports and "
"feature requests, file an :doc:`github_issues` entry instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:14 21e3485006bb4f5fa11b1124359a7763
msgid "Join the server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:32 a2979adb2376407b81d19a3a0ee84f54
msgid "The server's primary language is **English**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:36 69057eb177a247e2a3432ab15cf60cb9
msgid "Channel guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:38 221a31efe6514f5b9f87573abb514b6e
msgid ""
"The server has four categories. The list below describes what each "
"channel is *for* — most channels are quiet right now because the "
"community is just getting started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:42 8a6d815ef9f54d9197226fd04fddb0a0
msgid "**Information** — read-only announcements and ground rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:44 ebb2c0324896470db645e8837ad21f63
msgid "``#welcome`` — start here. Introduce yourself, say what you work on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:45 64a36e975cc246cfb4320d58d206cd9d
msgid ""
"``#announcements`` — releases, breaking changes, and event notices. "
"Maintainer-posted; turn on notifications if you depend on the library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:47 bc32626a80c840779d66846f63f05c1d
msgid "``#rules`` — server etiquette (see :ref:`etiquette` below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:49 7fae9f6299d7486fb18283119410ec97
msgid "**Community** — open conversation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:51 154bb13c510449f799ffbc0020317ab9
msgid ""
"``#general`` — anything TensorMesh-adjacent that doesn't fit elsewhere: "
"FEM discussion, PyTorch tricks, ML-for-PDE papers, related libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:53 e91af3e4523d4e1e96b341e802f67edb
msgid ""
"``#showcase`` — share what you built. Plots, animations, papers, blog "
"posts, course material — all welcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:56 0242cfea8a154654ba3c832761a617b4
msgid "**Help** — getting un-stuck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:58 6cfca174d7194b30a695df04b327f90c
msgid ""
"``#help`` — usage questions. \"How do I assemble X?\", \"Why doesn't my "
"mesh load?\", \"What's the right API for Y?\". See :ref:`asking-well` "
"below for what to include."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:61 4fb83059ad6843c78f0eba1e2aedbefc
msgid ""
"``#troubleshooting`` — installation issues, environment problems, "
"CUDA/torch version conflicts, build errors with the C++ sparse-solver "
"extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:65 64a71479373d4be6ab2db8c1e2f664f7
msgid "**Development** — for people writing patches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:67 714da4e1daf140149679a2e2fbacd4fc
msgid ""
"``#dev`` — design discussion, refactors-in-flight, RFC-style threads "
"before opening a PR. Maintainers and contributors hang out here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:69 5ab6cc7193394ac38ba62fbac4546ce6
msgid ""
"``#staff-only`` — private channel for maintainer coordination (release "
"planning, moderation). Listed here for transparency; you won't see it "
"unless you have the maintainer role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:77 bc55c812dfe3453b8af4a313e81f7215
msgid "Asking a good help question"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:79 834b7c25ec8d4a30a8592af33e9f1e98
msgid ""
"A few lines of context turn an unanswerable question into one a "
"maintainer can answer in a minute:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:82 1f803dc6f69a4b119dcf627876fcfe65
msgid ""
"**What you ran** — a minimal snippet, ideally something a reader can "
"paste into a Python shell. Triple-backtick formatting is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:84 b986dcd6e22f4ac98a316d238760369d
msgid ""
"**What you saw** — the full traceback, not a paraphrase. Wrap long output"
" in a code block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:86 a25ff46b99b54d61b23422aec4633715
msgid "**What you expected** — the shape, value, or behavior you were after."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:87 87688b53cd7949688ad6d2a5b9c60d01
msgid ""
"**Versions** — output of ``python -c \"import torch, torch_sla, "
"tensormesh; print(torch.__version__, torch_sla.__version__, "
"tensormesh.__version__)\"``, plus your OS and (if relevant) CUDA version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:91 8c44a74075a54a0fb118998331b3eb41
msgid ""
"If your question is longer than a few paragraphs or you'd like the answer"
" to be searchable later, post it to :doc:`github_discussions` and drop a "
"link in ``#help``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:99 8cc16792885342c3acc83de87361af5b
msgid "Server etiquette"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:101 44c80f17eb8c447b8d95a0f5e54b4b22
msgid "A short list of norms that keep the server pleasant:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:103 9a78ba6427ae41cb8aa3cc161fc741fd
msgid "Be kind and patient. Many users are learning FEM, PyTorch, or both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:104 bb18a1713c5845aaab19084b9e81c096
msgid "Keep technical disagreements technical."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:105 c56063017e0c46b6ad4b6b3ca7ffadc7
msgid "No spam, no promotion of unrelated products, no harassment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:106 00a6d576dbe24aefba7137fb21ec95df
msgid ""
"English is the default in public channels; please translate if you paste "
"a non-English error so others can help."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:109 a32efe86510b4901a91317b1a8721a16
msgid ""
"Maintainers may remove messages or members that violate these norms. If "
"you witness a problem, ping ``@moderator`` or DM a maintainer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:114 c8c84ac891154f4eb31601d9691e3ce3
msgid "Where chat doesn't fit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:116 62d0345e36ea4c3585f296ac3395b004
msgid ""
"Discord is great for live conversation, but the medium loses things: "
"messages scroll away, threads aren't always searchable, and Google "
"doesn't index them. So:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:120 dba7f2a570174fd1b56d786ca5091158
msgid ""
"**Bug?** → :doc:`github_issues`. Even a one-line repro on Discord should "
"end up as an issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:122 7854288376ac419f87ab208348c500e9
msgid "**Design discussion you want to last?** → :doc:`github_discussions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:123 0911b5a2bc6b4e309678154dba5ce3e6
msgid ""
"**Release announcements** live on the GitHub release page, not in chat "
"history — subscribe there if you want notifications you can't miss."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/discord.rst:127 1eedfae2da9546a2909a12a4950e5139
msgid "See you on the server."
msgstr ""

